Notes:
Moving to OPM

Noah spoke with OPM CISO Cord Chase. They may be able to get it under a 90-day ATO this week. Awaiting signature.

Noah spoke with Lisa and made sure she is caught up. Will continue to work with OPM until final hour to get system transferred. Noah will take any mtgs necessary with OPM mgmt if it helps them meet the deadline.

18F can help with transfer before 10/31.  Post 10/31, 18F team will not be under contract and will not be able to help with transfer. 
Technology risk assessment: The system is within the boundary of cloud.gov, and benefits from all the inherited cloud.gov and AWS controls.

Compliance risk assessment: The underlying components of the system properly leverage cloud.gov, and the underlying AWS. The system correctly implements 16-17 controls of the LATO baseline that are applicable. However the current queue between Infrastructure and GSA IT InfoSec teams will not be able to make room for the system in time. This is a potential audit finding, as currently policies and procedures dictate that GSA IT staff or contractors must conduct all final scans before the CISO will give any concurrance to an ATO. The system also uses deprecated authentication for backend users (MyUSA) and has not yet been hooked up to OPM's auth system or to the new cloud.gov auth.
